### Sample requests for the Real Estate Search Agent
### Use with VS Code "REST Client", JetBrains HTTP client, or copy into curl.
### Base URL assumes local run on port 3020.

@base = http://localhost:3020

### Health check
GET {{base}}/health

### 1. Happy path — rent, no agencies, near metro (primary demo)
# Expected: status "completed", ranked results from bazos + bezrealitky,
# Czech inquiry drafts for the top 3, full tool trace + token usage.
POST {{base}}/agent/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "2+kk Praha 5 do 25000 Kč, blízko metra, bez realitky"
}

### 2. Buyer search (sale)
# Expected: status "completed", criteria.dealType == "sale".
POST {{base}}/agent/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "Chci koupit 3+1 v Brně do 6 000 000 Kč"
}

### 3. English input
# Expected: status "completed", criteria parsed from English.
POST {{base}}/agent/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "1+kk to rent in Prague up to 18000 CZK, private owners only"
}

### 4. Refusal guardrail — out of scope
# Expected: status "refused", refusalReason set, no search/classify performed.
POST {{base}}/agent/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "write me a poem about the sea"
}

### 5. Input-validation guardrail — too short
# Expected: HTTP 400 (DTO @MinLength), the loop never starts.
POST {{base}}/agent/search
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "query": "hi"
}

### 6. List recent runs (observability)
GET {{base}}/agent/runs

### 7. Fetch one persisted run with its full trace
# Replace <runId> with a value returned by request #1.
GET {{base}}/agent/runs/<runId>
